## Marker genes

Pseudobulk marker genes were identified at resolution `r sel_res` using `edgeR`.
For each cluster, pseudobulk counts for cells in that cluster were compared against
all other clusters.

### Heatmaps of marker genes{.tabset}

```{r plot_marker_heatmaps, fig.height=9, fig.width=10, results="asis"}
for (nn in names(mkrs_ls)) {
  cat("#### ", nn, "\n")
  suppressMessages(draw(plot_heatmap_of_selected_genes(mkrs_dt, mkrs_ls[[nn]]),
    heatmap_legend_side = "bottom", annotation_legend_side = "bottom", merge_legend = TRUE))
  cat("\n\n")
}
```


### Highly variable genes{.tabset}

Normalised pseudobulk expression for the top 100 highly variable genes, in descending
order of variance.

```{r plot_hvgs, fig.height=8, fig.width=8, results="asis"}
n_pages = 10; per_p = 10; p = 1
for (i in seq(1, n_pages * per_p, by = per_p)) {
  cat('#### page', p, '\n'); p = p + 1
  sel_hvgs = pb_hvgs_dt[ i:(i + 9) ]
  print(plot_selected_genes(sel_hvgs, cpms_dt, cl_order = cl_ord))
  cat('\n\n')
}
```


### Top marker genes per cluster{.tabset}

Top 10 marker genes (FDR < 0.05, CPM ≥ `r min_cpm_mkr`) per cluster.

```{r plot_top_markers, fig.height=8, fig.width=8, results="asis"}
for (sel_cl in cl_ord) {
  cat('####', sel_cl, '\n')
  print(plot_top_marker_genes(sel_cl, top_min_dt, cpms_dt, cl_order = cl_ord))
  cat('\n\n')
}
```


## Gene set enrichment analysis{.tabset}

```{r plot_gsea, eval=do_gsea, include=do_gsea, fig.height=12, fig.width=8, results="asis"}
for (p in names(gsea_ls)) {
  if (is.null(gsea_ls[[p]])) next
  cat('### ', p, '\n')
  dt = gsea_ls[[p]] %>% .[ gsea_var == gsea_var_sel ]
  plot_gsea_dotplot(dt, gsea_cut = gsea_cut, n_top_paths = 5, max_nes = 2,
    size_range = c(10, 200), what = "pos_only", cl_order = cl_ord) %>% print
  cat('\n\n')
}
```


